<TITLE> White House spokesman Tony Snow stepping down </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINGTON, Aug 31 (Reuters) - White House Press Secretary Tony Snow, who has been battling cancer, plans to step down on Sept. 14 and he will be replaced his deputy, Dana Perino, a US official said. White House spokesman Tony Fratto confirmed that Snow would be departing and said President George W. Bush would announce the news later on Friday.
